Hey there,

Welcome to Hackatime!

In case you're not aware, Hackatime is Hack Club's coding time tracker. With it, you can start programming in your code editor and have your time set out in a neat dashboard.

Here are a few things you should do to get started:

- Set up your editor: https://hackatime.hackclub.com/my/wakatime_setup. You need to do this first! It's super easy to get started.
- Set a goal: https://hackatime.hackclub.com/my/settings/goals. You can set goals for specific time periods, languages, and projects. For instance, one goal I have is to code in Rust for at least 30 minutes a day.
- Set a theme: https://hackatime.hackclub.com/my/settings/. We have Catppuccin, GitHub Dark, Rose Pine, Nord and more!
- Import from WakaTime: https://hackatime.hackclub.com/my/settings/imports_exports to have your WakaTime stats show up in Hackatime! (optional)

If you need help with anything, feel free to reply to this email and we'll help you out as soon as we can.

Cheers,
the Hackatime team
